<section>
    <h2 id="cards">Cards</h2>
    <p>Different styled cards that are used on this site</p>

    <div class="card">
        <small>CSS Class: card</small>
        <p class="card-title">Basic card</p>
        <p class="card-text">This card has no background or hover features. It appears like normal text.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-hoverable">
        <small>CSS Classes: card card-hoverable</small>
        <p class="card-title">Basic card with hover effect</p>
        <p class="card-text">Place your mouse pointer over this card to see a neat hover effect!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-background">
        <small>CSS Classes: card card-background</small>
        <p class="card-title">Card with background</p>
        <p class="card-text">This card has a nice background! Notice how the text is aligned, but the card overflows into the margin.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-background card-hoverable">
        <small>CSS Classes: card card-background card-hoverable</small>
        <p class="card-title">Card with background and hover effect</p>
        <p class="card-text">Apply the previous hover effect to cards with backgrounds!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-background card-hoverable">
        <p class="card-title">Card with no metadata</p>
        <p class="card-text">This is the card text</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-background card-hoverable">
        <p class="card-text">Card with no title</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card card-background card-hoverable card-alert">
        <small>CSS Classes: card card-background card-hoverable card-alert</small>
        <p class="card-title">An alert styled card</p>
        <p class="card-text">This card is used as a call to action for important information that the reader should pay attention to</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 id="streams">Streams</h2>
    <p>Streams is kind of like a micro blogging section of this site (think X/Twitter), this section mockups how these will be rendered.</p>

    <div class="stream">
        <div class="stream-meta">
            <p class="stream-date">29<span>th</span> December 2023</p>
            <p class="stream-time">8:36<span>am</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="stream-main">
            <h3 class="stream-title">Stream with photos</h3>
            <p>Steams can have multiple paragraphs, like below.<br />Streams can also contain images</p>
            <div class="gallery">
                <img class="image pure-img" src="/images/gallery/nature/001.jpg" />
                <img class="image pure-img" src="/images/gallery/nature/002.jpg" />
                <img class="image pure-img" src="/images/gallery/nature/003.jpg" />
                <img class="image pure-img" src="/images/gallery/nature/004.jpg" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stream">
        <div class="stream-meta">
            <p class="stream-date">28<span>th</span> December 2023</p>
            <p class="stream-time">4:32<span>pm</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="stream-main">
            <h3 class="stream-title">My first mockup stream!</h3>
            <p>Idk where I'll pull this data through once built, but hey, at least I have a style mocked out!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

