<section>
    <h2 id="links">Link Interaction</h2>
    <p>
        Links must be contains within <a href="#">paragraph</a> tags to have applied styling. Links
        contain a special hover effect that includes the background within the animation.
        Hover over any of the <a href="#">links in this paragraph to test</a>. Links should be <a href="#">aligned</a> with the
        surrounding text. Links used the some hover animations as cards.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 id="code">Code</h2>
    <p>
        Since I'm a developer, displaying inline code snippers (without highlighting) is very helpful! These snippets
        can be used by themselves, in a list or within a paragraph <span class="code">like such</span> without affecting the surrounding content.
    </p>
    <p><span class="code">I'm some code!</span></p>
    <ul>
        <li><p><span class="code">command -useful</span></p></li>
        <li><p><span class="code">command -useful2</span></p></li>
        <li><p><span class="code">command -useful3</span></p></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        <pre>
This is some longer code
that takes over a few lines
created using the 'pre' element vs a span with a class of 'code'</pre>
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 id="forms">Forms</h2>
    <p>I don't do anything with forms on this website, but I've built out the style guide for when I do. Below is a basic form with two inputs and a submit button.</p>
    <p>This styling is built upon pure-css.</p>
    <form class="pure-form pure-form-stacked">
        <label for="fname">First name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" value="John">

        <label for="lname">Last name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" value="Doe">

        <button type="submit" class="pure-button pure-button-primary">Submit</button>
    </form>
</section>

